  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Early stroke rehabilitation is known to be an effective and essential therapy in gaining
      functional independence and preventing complications. However, there was no consensus of
      proper amount of language rehabilitation in stroke patients. In this study, the investigators
      investigated the effects of the intensive language rehabilitation during subacute phase to
      improve language function in patients with first-ever strokes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Intensive language rehabilitation group - language rehabilitation therapy by language
      therapist for 1 hours on every working day for 4 weeks

      Conventional language rehabilitation group

      - language rehabilitation therapy by language therapist for 30 minutes on every working day
      for 4 weeks
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
